What this project borrows from the upstream work
-------------------------------------------------
- The serial command protocol (COMMAND:FOCUSER:* / REPLY:FOCUSER:*)
  The protocol was reverse-engineered from the README and driver source
  references. No source code from the upstream ASCOM driver or firmware
  has been copied into this repository.

- The general concept and hardware design (28BYJ-48 stepper, ULN2003 board,
  herringbone gear approach, PETG material recommendation).

What this project does that is new and original
-----------------------------------------------
- Arduino firmware rewritten from scratch for the ESP32-S3 (Arduino Nano
  ESP32), including ESP32-specific EEPROM emulation, correct pin mapping,
  mandatory pinMode() calls, and verified motor de-energisation behaviour.

- INDI driver (C++) — a completely new implementation targeting Linux,
  PHD2, and KStars/Ekos. No ASCOM code is present or derived.

- Python serial test utility — written independently.

- udev rules — written independently.

- OpenSCAD 3D models for three telescopes (RVO Horizon 60 ED, Celestron
  NexStar 8SE, SkyWatcher Explorer 200P) — original designs, not derived
  from any upstream STL or CAD file.

The Celestron OAG STL files in the upstream repository were created by a
contributor (Endymion42) and are not reproduced here. If you use a Celestron
OAG, refer to the upstream repository for those specific 3D files.

